<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-49-0166 </DOCNO><TEXT>In October 1988 the conference Euroforum New Energies took place in Saarbruecken,Western Germany. Renewable energies researchers, financed by the EuropeanCommunity, discussed progress in the field of generation of solar energy,wind energy, biomass energy, geothermal energy and hydro energy. It canbe concluded that there is great progress. The market share of New Energiesis not yet big enough. According to persons concerned it is about timethat large-scale consumers and small-scale consumers discover the valueof renewable energy sources. 3 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>